-- Tam Airplane Makes Forced Landing After Suspected Bathroom Fire
-- B y   M a r i a   L u i z a   R a b e l l o
-- 2012-06-11T18:13:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-11/tam-airplane-makes-forced-landing-after-suspected-bathroom-fire.html
A Tam SA airplane made an emergency
landing in Brasilia today because of a suspected fire in a
restroom, the airline said in an e-mailed statement.  The airplane took off from  Rio de Janeiro  and was scheduled
to land in Belem, Para state, TAM said.  Globo news earlier reported that there were signs of fire
in two bathrooms.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Maria Luiza Rabello in Brasilia newsroom at 
